Description: DRUM ROLL PLEASE! This energy efficient home gives new meaning to comfort, and features the best use of 1360 square feet possible, including STORAGE GALORE: there's an astounding 3 closets IN THE MASTER BEDROOM alone! Home is in the finishing stages of a complete remodel, including all new hardwood or carpet and fresh paint throughout. When this home is done, MOVE-IN-READY will be the UNDERSTATEMENT of the year...all that's missing is YOU! Time to move to the north side; just don't trip on the remodelers!

The charm of the 1920's, but the convenience of today!  Updated and modernized 3 bed 2 bath home has newly installed 6-ton HVAC with 2-stage efficiency furnace, custom concrete countertops, stainless steel farm-sink, gas/electric connect for oven/range, retextured & painted interior, new insulated interior & exterior doors, new above ground PEX plumbing, upgraded electric panel, new electrical receptables & switches throughout, and new covered front porch & back deck round out these upgrades/updates.

Majesty and splendor in Heritage Hills. The history of this 1906 home is the history of OKC. Lovingly tended to by the five families who have called it home, this is a generational home with an easy elegance and it awaits its next chapter. The main residence is three stories, restored and renovated with meticulous attention to historic detail. The original door knocker welcomes into a pretty foyer, beyond which is living, dining, library, kitchen, morning room and large den. Elegant arched doors, original and restored hardwoods and molding, pocket doors. Eight mantels throughout including a circa 1840 Biedermeier. Four bedrooms including the glorious primary suite on the second floor. Up one level is a theater quality screening room, large studio and childrenâ€™s performance stage. Huge three-car garage with apartment above with full kitchen, bedroom and ensuite bath that is included in marketed square footage. Corner lot with elegant landscape brick sidewalks. A truly rare opportunity.

If your dreaming of starting your own business, this is the place for you. There is a manger's house. In the main house property there are 3 floors, the main floor has office, stage, 1/2 bath and a huge room divided (that could be easily opened back up. On the top floor you will find it separated into different areas,(which could easily be opened up again) also on the 2nd floor there is a full bath and a 1/2 bath.  Downstairs you will find the kitchen and a separate room.

Country living in the32x80  16 ' Wide remodeled home with vaulted ceilings that is a must to see. The countertops and final stages are being completed .
